column4: Welcome, you are now talking to an AI doctor. As I am part of a scientific experiment, I would appreciate it if you could take the time to answer a super short questionnaire at the end of the interview. Tap Speak to ask your question and then tap Send to submit it to me.
I'm sorry you feel that way. I'm here to answer questions about medical issues in order to provide helpful guidance.
i sometimes get stabbing headaches in my left temple and behind my left

That sounds like a symptom of migraine headaches. Common symptoms of migraines include a throbbing, pulsating sensation on one side of your head as well as nausea, vomiting, and sensitivity to light and sound. If you are having these symptoms, it would be advised to speak with your doctor for a proper diagnosis and treatment plan.
